WEBVTT

00:26.375 --> 00:28.457
<i>One, two, three</i>

00:28.458 --> 00:31.457
<i>My baby don't mess around
Because she loves me so</i>

00:31.458 --> 00:33.791
<i>And this I know fo sho...</i>

00:36.708 --> 00:39.707
Okay, the key
to my world-famous French toast,

00:39.708 --> 00:41.790
you put cinnamon right into the batter.

00:41.791 --> 00:42.957
Got it.

00:42.958 --> 00:44.290
Wait, what's "bladder"?

00:44.291 --> 00:47.666
"Batter" is a mix of milk and eggs.

00:48.791 --> 00:52.458
Hmm. Tastes kinda fishy.

00:55.458 --> 00:56.375
Boop!

00:57.458 --> 01:00.207
Ooh, Stevie, I got a big one.

01:00.208 --> 01:02.416
Oh, Stevie, look, look!

01:05.250 --> 01:06.082
No! No tickling!

01:06.083 --> 01:07.166
Fish tickles!

01:12.625 --> 01:16.040
<i>I mean, come on.
We're like one of those happy families</i>

01:16.041 --> 01:18.499
<i>you see at the beginning
of a disaster movie.</i>

01:18.500 --> 01:20.750
<i>Everything is perfect.</i>

01:21.500 --> 01:24.665
<i>Until... the disaster.</i>

01:24.666 --> 01:26.499
- Oh, what's wrong, honey?
- Huh?

01:26.500 --> 01:29.540
<i>Okay, so I'm not blaming
my little brother here,</i>

01:29.541 --> 01:32.540
<i>but he definitely didn't make life easier.</i>

01:32.541 --> 01:35.875
- Paci. He needs his paci.
- Oh! Huh?

01:38.291 --> 01:41.583
<i>Oh, I should
probably tell you. This is a dream.</i>

01:51.333 --> 01:53.415
- Help me find the one he likes.
- He has a preference?

01:53.416 --> 01:54.957
Yes, the blue handle.

01:54.958 --> 01:56.540
Uh, they're all blue.

01:56.541 --> 01:58.875
It's the one that sounds like
a bad birthday clown.

01:59.541 --> 02:02.165
I charge extra for balloon animals.

02:02.166 --> 02:03.540
Hmm! Hi-ya!

02:03.541 --> 02:05.665
<i>They say dreams are the mind's way</i>

02:05.666 --> 02:07.749
<i>of trying to fix your problems
in the real world.</i>

02:07.750 --> 02:09.415
The perfect cartwheel.

02:09.416 --> 02:10.833
I'm just so proud.

02:12.333 --> 02:15.415
Yah! Whoa! Hi-yah!

02:15.416 --> 02:18.082
<i>And fixing things is kinda my thing.</i>

02:18.083 --> 02:19.165
Got it!

02:19.166 --> 02:21.457
It's not the paci. He probably wants...

02:21.458 --> 02:23.540
<i>But, lately, all my dreams...</i>

02:23.541 --> 02:26.333
<i>...keep turning into nightmares.</i>

02:27.083 --> 02:29.875
Okay, it's not the stuffy.
Uh, maybe he's hungry?

02:30.916 --> 02:32.999
Honey, did you forget
to pay the house bill?

02:33.000 --> 02:34.915
- I thought you paid it.
- You said you would.

02:34.916 --> 02:37.624
No, no, I said I could, but then
I figured you would, so I didn't.

02:37.625 --> 02:38.625
Michael!

02:41.750 --> 02:43.290
Mom! Dad!

02:43.291 --> 02:45.916
<i>Maybe they're trying to tell me something.</i>

02:53.375 --> 02:54.208
<i>Or maybe...</i>

02:56.625 --> 02:58.041
<i>it's just a dream.</i>

03:01.500 --> 03:02.832
Shoot.

03:02.833 --> 03:04.750
Okay, careful, I'll get the broom.

03:06.750 --> 03:08.207
No, Jenn, I got it.

03:08.208 --> 03:09.499
No, I got it.

03:09.500 --> 03:12.583
Giant hot dog, don't eat me.

03:21.000 --> 03:24.415
I know things are tight,
but we're getting by.

03:24.416 --> 03:25.957
As soon as I finish the album--

03:25.958 --> 03:27.957
It's-- It's been two years.

03:27.958 --> 03:29.665
I could've finished it

03:29.666 --> 03:32.082
if my lead singer
didn't just give up on me.

03:32.083 --> 03:34.165
I didn't give up on you, Michael.

03:34.166 --> 03:35.499
I believe in you.

03:35.500 --> 03:38.291
I-- I really do.

03:39.708 --> 03:41.708
But things are different now.

03:43.208 --> 03:45.541
Something's gotta change.

03:53.041 --> 03:54.166
<i>Change?</i>

03:54.666 --> 03:55.916
<i>What does that mean?</i>

03:56.916 --> 03:59.250
<i>All parents argue. It's not a big deal.</i>

04:01.708 --> 04:02.541
<i>Right?</i>

04:07.958 --> 04:11.625
<i>Maybe they just need to remember
how great things used to be.</i>

04:24.791 --> 04:28.124
<i>Don't worry about me
Yeah, I'll be fine</i>

04:28.125 --> 04:30.832
<i>I read enough books for seven lives</i>

04:30.833 --> 04:33.790
<i>I know that I'll make it out okay</i>

04:33.791 --> 04:36.624
<i>I'm dancing my way through every day</i>

04:36.625 --> 04:37.916
<i>'Cause I...</i>

04:41.291 --> 04:42.291
Eww!

04:43.000 --> 04:45.124
Elliot!

04:45.125 --> 04:47.666
Oh, my God, this is just so gross.

04:48.416 --> 04:52.124
Could you not leave a trail of rancid meat
festering on the floor?

04:52.125 --> 04:56.040
But how else is Baloney Tony
gonna find his way home?

04:56.041 --> 04:58.083
He's a stuffed animal!

04:59.750 --> 05:01.707
I miss you, Baloney Tony.

05:01.708 --> 05:03.083
Wherever you are.

05:04.375 --> 05:07.625
Morning, Bear, Bear Jr., Barely There.

05:08.791 --> 05:09.958
Frank.

05:14.416 --> 05:15.458
Ooh!

05:16.333 --> 05:20.833
<i>Every night, I sleep to dream...</i>

05:21.958 --> 05:24.707
<i>Of you and me</i>

05:24.708 --> 05:26.457
- Hey! Wanna see a magic trick?
- Ahh! Ugh.

05:26.458 --> 05:27.957
Why do you have to be so annoying?

05:27.958 --> 05:29.666
Open the note, Stevie.

05:32.125 --> 05:35.207
"Stevie will say, 'Why do you
have to be so--'" Okay, we're done here.

05:35.208 --> 05:36.540
Ta-da!

05:36.541 --> 05:37.540
Still annoying.

05:37.541 --> 05:40.040
Well, thank you. Can I help?

05:40.041 --> 05:42.957
No, no, no. It's okay.
This has to be perfect.

05:42.958 --> 05:45.499
Come on! Dad taught me
to cook French toast too.

05:45.500 --> 05:46.665
I can flip 'em.

05:46.666 --> 05:48.374
Give it back! You're gonna ruin it.

05:48.375 --> 05:50.457
Oh! Elliot!

05:50.458 --> 05:52.624
I mean it. Give it back!

05:52.625 --> 05:55.083
Oh, no!

05:55.791 --> 05:56.957
Ow!

05:56.958 --> 05:59.458
- Not my fault.
- Elliot!

06:00.541 --> 06:01.540
I've got an idea.

06:01.541 --> 06:06.541
How about you do some real magic
and make yourself disappear?

06:09.458 --> 06:12.333
Hmm. A disappearing act.

06:13.875 --> 06:14.708
Whoa!

06:29.666 --> 06:31.750
<i>Can you remember when we were young?</i>

06:33.541 --> 06:35.832
Oh, hey, sweetheart. You're up early.

06:35.833 --> 06:38.708
Yeah, uh, Mom made you breakfast.

06:40.000 --> 06:41.000
Seriously?

06:42.000 --> 06:42.832
Knock, knock.

06:42.833 --> 06:45.749
Oh, good.
You've come to save me. Okay, quick.

06:45.750 --> 06:47.207
Name a letter from A to F.

06:47.208 --> 06:49.832
I can't grade your students' papers.

06:49.833 --> 06:51.415
Come on. Just one?

06:51.416 --> 06:54.624
I mean, this 12-year-old
thinks Prince is overrated.

06:54.625 --> 06:55.541
Oh.

06:56.166 --> 06:57.041
Automatic fail.

06:59.500 --> 07:02.040
Hey, it says, "Take a break."

07:02.041 --> 07:04.208
'Cause Dad made you breakfast.

07:05.958 --> 07:06.791
Seriously?

07:07.291 --> 07:08.875
Famous French toast.

07:09.500 --> 07:10.665
Just like old times, huh?

07:10.666 --> 07:14.250
Yeah. Just like old times.

07:15.708 --> 07:16.875
Hey, where's Elliot?

07:19.166 --> 07:20.457
Oh, I don't know.

07:20.458 --> 07:23.249
Where could he be? It's like he just--

07:23.250 --> 07:24.415
Disappeared!

07:24.416 --> 07:28.040
Ha-ha! Elliot the Extraordinary
strikes again!

07:28.041 --> 07:30.250
Elliot.

07:32.833 --> 07:35.790
Hey, guys, um, while we're all together,

07:35.791 --> 07:37.249
something came up,

07:37.250 --> 07:40.290
and I'm, uh,
headed out of town super early tomorrow.

07:40.291 --> 07:41.416
You're leaving?

07:42.041 --> 07:44.832
Well, the university in Duluth is looking
for an associate professor,

07:44.833 --> 07:46.832
which is, you know, kind of a big step up.

07:46.833 --> 07:49.957
But I thought I'd check it out
and go see Grandma while I'm there.

07:49.958 --> 07:53.124
But it's so far away,
and Dad hates Duluth.

07:53.125 --> 07:56.750
What? No, no, I love any town
that has "Dull" right there in the name.

07:58.250 --> 08:00.583
I'm kidding. I'm kidding. It's great!

08:01.125 --> 08:03.082
<i>Oh, no. That's Dad's fake smile.</i>

08:03.083 --> 08:05.332
<i>You can tell
by the way his eyes get weird.</i>

08:05.333 --> 08:07.874
<i>See? Looks like a dead possum.</i>

08:07.875 --> 08:09.540
And while Mom's in Duluth,

08:09.541 --> 08:12.415
you guys are getting an all-access pass

08:12.416 --> 08:15.749
to a VIP named D-A-D.

08:15.750 --> 08:19.582
And I've got prime seats lined up
at Polly's Pizzeria!

08:19.583 --> 08:20.499
Yes!

08:20.500 --> 08:23.457
<i>Polly's Pizzeria A place for family fun</i>

08:23.458 --> 08:26.208
Minors must be accompanied by an adult.

08:28.500 --> 08:31.249
You're definitely in charge
while I'm gone.

08:31.250 --> 08:34.374
Are you and Dad okay?

08:34.375 --> 08:36.249
- Is this about money?
- What?

08:36.250 --> 08:40.124
I-- I could get a job. I could babysit.
Or work at the mall.

08:40.125 --> 08:43.207
I could buy a fake ID on the dark web
to subvert child labor laws--

08:43.208 --> 08:45.665
Oh, Stevie, Stevie.
It's just an interview.

08:45.666 --> 08:48.749
I mean, it doesn't mean it's happening.
They might not even want me.

08:48.750 --> 08:52.000
I mean, have you seen
my serious interview face?

08:54.833 --> 08:55.791
Okay?

08:57.541 --> 09:00.665
Oh, and while I'm gone, can you help
Elliot find a book for his report?

09:00.666 --> 09:04.041
And nothing about
bodily functions or pirates.

09:04.958 --> 09:07.208
Or the bodily functions of pirates.

09:08.375 --> 09:09.208
Yeah.

09:10.291 --> 09:11.125
Sure.

09:12.041 --> 09:14.499
It's just an interview.
Mom and Dad'll figure this out.

09:14.500 --> 09:15.790
What if they don't?

09:15.791 --> 09:18.958
No, no, no, it's gonna be fine.
Fine, fine, fine!

09:19.500 --> 09:20.582
Be cool.

09:20.583 --> 09:22.749
Hey, Stevie!

09:22.750 --> 09:24.915
You're supposed to help me
find a book for my report.

09:24.916 --> 09:27.665
Oh, yeah, 'cause there's nothing
more important than that.

09:27.666 --> 09:30.832
It's cool.
I've got a solid C in that class anyway.

09:30.833 --> 09:32.707
Ahh!

09:32.708 --> 09:33.625
Elliot.

09:34.250 --> 09:36.540
You can't bring home a C.

09:36.541 --> 09:38.875
I can if I apply myself.

09:40.750 --> 09:43.332
Classics. You gotta stick
with the classics.

09:43.333 --> 09:45.457
Teachers eat that stuff up.

09:45.458 --> 09:46.541
Got it.

09:47.208 --> 09:48.083
Ooh!

09:49.166 --> 09:51.582
Flying bed. Classic.

09:51.583 --> 09:53.999
Cowboys! Classic.

09:54.000 --> 09:56.124
<i>Fists of Dynamite?</i> Class--

09:56.125 --> 09:58.832
Oh, wait. It's a metaphor?

09:58.833 --> 10:01.833
Call me when your fists actually explode.

10:14.416 --> 10:15.416
No.

10:16.041 --> 10:17.249
Nope.

10:17.250 --> 10:19.332
No way!

10:19.333 --> 10:21.415
A poster for Mom and Dad's first show!

10:21.416 --> 10:24.582
Elliot, check this out. Uh, Elliot?

10:24.583 --> 10:27.207
Uh, welcome to Shiver Me Thrifters...

10:27.208 --> 10:30.458
...where your trash is our treasure.

10:33.833 --> 10:36.583
Can I help you plunder your way
to big, big savings?

10:37.166 --> 10:38.124
All good hair.

10:38.125 --> 10:41.707
I mean, here.
Sorry. I'm just looking for a boy.

10:41.708 --> 10:44.499
Brother! Boy. Uh, my brother, he's a boy.

10:44.500 --> 10:45.415
Obviously.

10:45.416 --> 10:49.082
Uh, anyways, you have been a huge help.

10:49.083 --> 10:51.250
Love you. I mean, thank you. Oh!

10:52.041 --> 10:53.333
I'm fine. Ow!

10:55.958 --> 10:58.000
Whoa.

11:00.625 --> 11:02.415
Ladies and gentlemen,

11:02.416 --> 11:05.874
introducing Elliot the Extraord--

11:05.875 --> 11:08.416
Huh?

11:26.833 --> 11:27.915
Elliot!

11:27.916 --> 11:30.999
- What are you doing down here?
- Oh, it's just you.

11:31.000 --> 11:32.332
What is that?

11:32.333 --> 11:34.041
Hey, give it back!

11:34.750 --> 11:40.082
<i>"The Legend of the Sandman,
the Giver of Dreams"?</i>

11:40.083 --> 11:43.207
It's mostly pictures, Elliot.
This isn't a real book.

11:43.208 --> 11:44.750
Hmm?

11:57.791 --> 11:59.665
<i>Mr. Sandman...</i>

11:59.666 --> 12:02.915
- Whoa. Magic!
- <i>Bring me your dreams...</i>

12:02.916 --> 12:07.165
Stupid circuit breaker. Every day.

12:07.166 --> 12:09.290
Hey, you're not supposed to be down here.

12:09.291 --> 12:12.582
You're not supposed to be down hair!
I mean, here.

12:12.583 --> 12:13.749
Hmm?

12:13.750 --> 12:16.957
Watch as we disappear!

12:16.958 --> 12:18.749
Run!

12:18.750 --> 12:20.582
No. Stop.

12:20.583 --> 12:23.916
If I get in trouble,
I might lose this fantastic job.

12:28.000 --> 12:31.040
Okay. Which book do you wanna do?

12:31.041 --> 12:32.207
This one!

12:32.208 --> 12:33.583
Where did you get that?

12:34.750 --> 12:36.790
Sleight of hand.

12:36.791 --> 12:38.374
You stole--

12:38.375 --> 12:40.790
You stole it? Are you crazy?

12:40.791 --> 12:42.915
The tag said it was priceless.

12:42.916 --> 12:46.208
That obviously means it's free. Duh!

12:49.291 --> 12:50.624
Hey, check this out.

12:50.625 --> 12:53.665
It says the Sandman
can make your dreams come true.

12:53.666 --> 12:55.291
- What?
- Right there.

12:56.333 --> 12:59.207
"Sandman, please, I call unto you."

12:59.208 --> 13:01.250
"Grant me my dreams,

13:01.958 --> 13:03.875
make them come true."

13:07.875 --> 13:09.040
Whoa.

13:09.041 --> 13:12.165
Do you know what this means?

13:12.166 --> 13:13.125
What?

13:13.875 --> 13:14.833
Stevie?

13:15.333 --> 13:16.583
What, Stevie? What?

13:17.416 --> 13:18.874
You're really gullible.

13:18.875 --> 13:20.000
No, I'm not!

13:20.541 --> 13:21.750
Wait, what does that mean?

13:24.166 --> 13:26.250
Oh, man.

13:28.666 --> 13:33.040
If the Sandman made my dreams come true,
I'd have a jetpack,

13:33.041 --> 13:34.374
a six-pack,

13:34.375 --> 13:38.665
and, like, my fists
would be made out of actual dynamite.

13:38.666 --> 13:41.207
You want dynamite fists?

13:41.208 --> 13:42.916
What would your dream be?

13:49.333 --> 13:52.083
Uh, Stevie, what would your dream be?

13:53.750 --> 13:54.958
My own room.

14:09.583 --> 14:13.625
Elliot, go back to bed.

14:15.041 --> 14:17.333
Elliot, what are you doing?

14:20.250 --> 14:21.500
Elliot, wake up!

14:23.375 --> 14:24.291
Elliot!

14:25.791 --> 14:27.125
- What?
- Look!

14:40.041 --> 14:41.957
This can't be happening.

14:41.958 --> 14:44.624
This is totally happening!

14:44.625 --> 14:48.000
Ooh! Ooh! Ooh! Yee-haw!

14:48.583 --> 14:49.625
No, no, no! Wait!

14:50.291 --> 14:51.500
Wait!

14:52.916 --> 14:54.500
Oh!

15:03.750 --> 15:05.540
Oh!

15:05.541 --> 15:08.040
Whoa! Whoa!

15:08.041 --> 15:09.790
I didn't know you could do parkour.

15:09.791 --> 15:10.708
I can't!

15:17.041 --> 15:17.916
Whoa!

15:25.583 --> 15:26.458
Ugh!

15:28.708 --> 15:30.250
Elliot!

15:30.958 --> 15:33.332
I can fly it?

15:33.333 --> 15:35.957
I can fly it!

15:35.958 --> 15:38.166
Whoa-ho!

15:42.291 --> 15:44.207
I'm gonna kill you!

15:44.208 --> 15:45.125
Gotcha!

15:46.541 --> 15:49.540
Elliot, take us down!

15:49.541 --> 15:52.165
Oh, you wanna go down?

15:52.166 --> 15:54.166
Then let's go down!

16:09.500 --> 16:11.000
Hi, doggie!

16:14.000 --> 16:15.333
Up, up, up, up!

16:20.500 --> 16:22.333
This thing is like a rocket!

16:23.875 --> 16:26.082
A rocket would be very cool.

16:26.083 --> 16:27.665
No, it wouldn't. Wait, what's that?

16:27.666 --> 16:28.875
Oh.

16:29.875 --> 16:32.374
It would probably be irresponsible

16:32.375 --> 16:34.040
for me to push this.

16:34.041 --> 16:35.083
Elliot, don't.

17:06.333 --> 17:08.040
Hey, look! That's our house.

17:08.041 --> 17:10.665
No, wait. That one has a pool.

17:10.666 --> 17:13.207
Why don't we have a pool? Are we poor?

17:13.208 --> 17:15.458
Forget that. Look at this.

17:28.000 --> 17:29.958
Whoa.

17:35.041 --> 17:36.708
What did you do?

17:51.666 --> 17:52.708
Come!

17:53.458 --> 17:54.500
Find me.

17:55.666 --> 17:59.333
And your dreams will come true.

18:02.875 --> 18:06.165
Whoa! Was that the Sandman?

18:06.166 --> 18:07.916
I don't know.

18:08.541 --> 18:09.666
Let's go find him!

18:12.250 --> 18:13.124
Or not.

18:13.125 --> 18:14.833
<i>Wake up.</i>

18:17.583 --> 18:19.457
<i>Wake up. Wake up.</i>

18:19.458 --> 18:21.915
<i>Wake up. Wake up!</i>

18:21.916 --> 18:23.290
Stevie?

18:23.291 --> 18:25.375
<i>Wake up!</i>

18:52.041 --> 18:54.665
I just had the craziest dream.

18:54.666 --> 18:56.290
Me too.

18:56.291 --> 18:57.957
Mine was awesome!

18:57.958 --> 18:59.374
Mine was awful.

18:59.375 --> 19:00.957
My bed was alive!

19:00.958 --> 19:03.665
It was like a wild animal, and I tamed it,

19:03.666 --> 19:06.165
and I pulled on the sheets,
and it started flying!

19:06.166 --> 19:07.332
And you.

19:07.333 --> 19:09.290
You were hanging on like,

19:09.291 --> 19:11.874
"Elliot, stop!"

19:11.875 --> 19:14.374
And there were these awesome stars,

19:14.375 --> 19:17.207
and they turned into the Sandman
from the book, and he said--

19:17.208 --> 19:20.375
"Find me and your dreams will come true."

19:22.083 --> 19:23.624
How'd you know that?

19:23.625 --> 19:26.291
We had the exact same dream.

19:27.000 --> 19:29.290
But that's not possible, right?

19:29.291 --> 19:32.333
Oh, my gosh! The Sandman is real!

19:33.208 --> 19:36.208
We both read the book last night.

19:36.833 --> 19:38.624
That's why we had the same dream.

19:38.625 --> 19:42.916
Or it's magic!

19:43.875 --> 19:45.833
I can see your crack, Houdini.

20:03.000 --> 20:03.958
Jenn.

20:05.666 --> 20:07.582
We have to talk about this.

20:07.583 --> 20:10.207
Okay, I have to go
if I'm gonna make this interview.

20:10.208 --> 20:11.625
Can I say one thing?

20:12.500 --> 20:14.499
Our-- Our life is here.

20:14.500 --> 20:17.582
We wrote our best songs here.
Our kids were born here.

20:17.583 --> 20:19.790
This... This is home.

20:19.791 --> 20:21.499
How could we leave that behind?

20:21.500 --> 20:23.207
Because things change.

20:23.208 --> 20:25.207
This would be a good job that pays more.

20:25.208 --> 20:27.458
The kids would be
in a better school district, and I...

20:28.333 --> 20:32.166
It might be good for us
to have a fresh start.

20:33.875 --> 20:37.375
You know, I'm just trying to do
what is best for our family.

20:38.750 --> 20:40.291
So am I.

20:42.208 --> 20:43.916
If you wanna move there,

20:44.791 --> 20:48.083
I don't know if I can do it.

20:52.333 --> 20:55.375
I... I... I gotta go.

21:19.000 --> 21:20.916
Ugh! No.

21:58.333 --> 22:01.665
Sandman, please, I call unto you.

22:01.666 --> 22:05.000
Grant me my dreams, make them come true.

22:44.291 --> 22:48.332
Hey, Dad!
There's a dead girl in the cereal.

22:48.333 --> 22:49.582
Tell your mother.

22:49.583 --> 22:51.165
Can I keep her?

22:51.166 --> 22:52.083
No!

22:53.208 --> 22:54.915
Oh, good. You're alive.

22:54.916 --> 22:56.750
Dad said I could keep you.

23:01.458 --> 23:03.333
All good. I'm all...

23:04.083 --> 23:05.208
good.

23:09.083 --> 23:10.124
Fresh squeezed!

23:10.125 --> 23:14.832
Oh, my gosh, I did it! It worked!

23:14.833 --> 23:16.207
Hi!

23:16.208 --> 23:17.916
It's all so perfect!

23:18.666 --> 23:20.332
It's Breakfast Town.

23:20.333 --> 23:22.124
I used to love this dream.

23:22.125 --> 23:23.582
I have sprinkles!

23:23.583 --> 23:26.040
Oh-ho-ho-ho! I'm finally a real doughnut!

23:26.041 --> 23:27.540
Hey, girl!

23:27.541 --> 23:29.332
Aw, who's a good sausage doggie?

23:29.333 --> 23:32.416
You are. Yes, you are. You smell so good.

23:37.541 --> 23:38.541
What a weird kid.

23:39.958 --> 23:40.915
All right.

23:40.916 --> 23:43.290
I'm coming for you, Sandman!

23:43.291 --> 23:46.832
If you can dream it,
you can do it, Stevie.

23:46.833 --> 23:48.833
Ha-ha! I can do it.

23:50.666 --> 23:51.832
What up, weirdo?

23:51.833 --> 23:54.082
No!

23:54.083 --> 23:57.290
No, no, no! Why are you here?

23:57.291 --> 23:59.665
I don't know.
I fell asleep, and here I am.

23:59.666 --> 24:02.040
Off, off. Down, down.

24:02.041 --> 24:04.582
Elliot, keep this thing away from me.

24:04.583 --> 24:07.332
Don't worry. I trained her. Check it out.

24:07.333 --> 24:09.666
Sit. Shake.

24:10.291 --> 24:11.250
Play bed.

24:11.958 --> 24:12.915
Ta-da!

24:12.916 --> 24:16.582
Wow! Now go away.
I'm gonna find the Sandman.

24:16.583 --> 24:19.290
I knew he was real. How do we find him?

24:19.291 --> 24:21.082
There is no we.

24:21.083 --> 24:22.207
Come on, girl.

24:22.208 --> 24:24.957
Sandman! Oh, Sandman. Where are you?

24:24.958 --> 24:26.665
Ugh. That's not how dreams work.

24:26.666 --> 24:29.500
- I know the Sandman!
- What? Who said that?

24:30.541 --> 24:33.291
- Is that our fridge?
- I'm in the back.

24:40.125 --> 24:41.624
Ew, gross.

24:41.625 --> 24:43.875
Smells familiar.

24:44.375 --> 24:46.624
Okay, it is just fine.

24:46.625 --> 24:48.415
Just a little dusty back here.

24:48.416 --> 24:51.500
I'm not gonna look at that.

24:52.166 --> 24:53.166
Hey, my retainer.

24:54.791 --> 24:57.125
I'm a perfect princess.

24:57.625 --> 24:59.957
Okay.

24:59.958 --> 25:02.915
Keep walking. No eye contact.
Is she still looking at us?

25:02.916 --> 25:05.375
Uh, yep. Still looking.

25:05.875 --> 25:08.624
- Oh!
- Hey! Help me out, will ya?

25:08.625 --> 25:10.290
Get me up! Get me up! Get me up!

25:10.291 --> 25:12.207
Okay, I push, you pull.

25:12.208 --> 25:14.582
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah. Yeah!

25:14.583 --> 25:16.625
Oh!

25:20.083 --> 25:24.458
<i>With these hungry eyes</i>

25:26.500 --> 25:29.874
<i>One look at you and I can't disguise</i>

25:29.875 --> 25:33.958
<i>I've got hungry eyes</i>

25:35.166 --> 25:38.707
<i>I feel the magic between you and I</i>

25:38.708 --> 25:42.416
<i>I've got hungry eyes</i>

25:46.625 --> 25:48.290
My man Smelliot!

25:48.291 --> 25:50.790
Baloney Tony! I love this dream.

25:50.791 --> 25:52.999
I feel so alive!

25:53.000 --> 25:55.957
Ah! That's the good stuff.

25:55.958 --> 25:58.040
I knew I smelled something rotten.

25:58.041 --> 26:00.207
Nice to see you too, Joanne.

26:00.208 --> 26:01.540
Stevie.

26:01.541 --> 26:03.207
That's what I said. Joanne.

26:03.208 --> 26:04.165
- Ste...
- Jo...

26:04.166 --> 26:05.290
- ...vie.
- ...anne.

26:05.291 --> 26:08.707
- I feel like we're saying the same thing.
- I've been looking all over for you.

26:08.708 --> 26:10.624
I've been stuck
back here eating dust bunnies

26:10.625 --> 26:13.040
and getting my toes tickled
by some deranged muffin.

26:13.041 --> 26:14.790
I see you, Delilah! I see you!

26:14.791 --> 26:18.082
Perfect princess.

26:18.083 --> 26:19.832
That's right, just keep walking.

26:19.833 --> 26:22.832
Ah, there I go. Sometimes I fall apart
when I get emotional.

26:22.833 --> 26:25.208
You know how it is.
Talk amongst yourselves.

26:26.166 --> 26:28.957
There. Good. We're good.

26:28.958 --> 26:30.749
Hey, how'd you get stuck back here?

26:30.750 --> 26:33.457
Someone stuck me back here
in the real world.

26:33.458 --> 26:34.624
Hmm.

26:34.625 --> 26:37.082
Joanne. Your sister. Standing right there.

26:37.083 --> 26:38.916
Okay, back you go.

26:40.541 --> 26:42.457
Want a piece of me? Take that!

26:42.458 --> 26:44.457
It was you!

26:44.458 --> 26:46.415
Yes, it was me.

26:46.416 --> 26:50.457
And I'd do it again because he smells
like a dumpster fire full of bad meat.

26:50.458 --> 26:52.874
Oh, stop! Go on.

26:52.875 --> 26:55.457
Can you just tell me
how to get to the Sandman?

26:55.458 --> 26:58.874
Yeah, but you'll never get there.
Take my advice, forget about the Sandman.

26:58.875 --> 27:00.957
Go have fun
with your delusional brunch buddies

27:00.958 --> 27:03.207
so E and I can blow stuff up
with laser farts.

27:03.208 --> 27:04.374
- Yay-- Ow!
- Ow!

27:04.375 --> 27:07.790
- That's it.
- Okay, okay, let's chill!

27:07.791 --> 27:10.250
A "please" would be nice.

27:11.791 --> 27:14.374
Okay, that was just a strong wind.

27:14.375 --> 27:15.375
Follow me.

27:17.166 --> 27:18.707
The Sandman lives there.

27:18.708 --> 27:19.874
Okay. Easy enough.

27:19.875 --> 27:22.915
But if you try to find the Sandman,

27:22.916 --> 27:26.250
your dream will 100% turn into

27:27.416 --> 27:29.540
a nightmare.

27:29.541 --> 27:32.290
A nightmare?
I don't wanna be in a nightmare.

27:32.291 --> 27:35.082
Me neither. I got enough drama here
with the crazy muffins.

27:35.083 --> 27:37.999
A little nightmare isn't gonna stop me.

27:38.000 --> 27:41.333
Ooh! Scary!

27:42.416 --> 27:44.458
That's gonna be expensive.

27:45.750 --> 27:48.041
Oh! What is happening?

27:49.708 --> 27:53.375
I'm not with her! She has no friends.
Who could love a face like that?

28:00.291 --> 28:01.457
It's Nightmara!

28:01.458 --> 28:04.540
I mean, it's Nightmara,
the giver of nightmares.

28:04.541 --> 28:07.291
You have to get through her
if you wanna reach the Sandman.

28:13.416 --> 28:15.415
Coming through!

28:15.416 --> 28:16.624
Scramble!

28:16.625 --> 28:19.332
- What's happening?
- She's trying to wake us up.

28:19.333 --> 28:21.291
What's the matter, Stevie?

28:22.458 --> 28:25.833
I thought you liked breakfast!

28:34.208 --> 28:38.290
Oh, what? Avocados are making
zombie babies now?

28:38.291 --> 28:40.374
Perfect princess!

28:40.375 --> 28:42.291
It's even worse back here!

28:44.333 --> 28:45.500
Tony!

28:46.000 --> 28:46.957
I got this.

28:46.958 --> 28:50.582
I can feel the power of the dreamverse
flowing through my stuffing.

28:50.583 --> 28:52.915
Get behind me,
because I'm gonna channel it

28:52.916 --> 28:56.041
into an epic flaming fireball!

28:59.958 --> 29:00.875
Ew.

29:01.625 --> 29:04.208
So, you, uh,

29:04.875 --> 29:06.290
seen good movies lately? Anybody?

29:06.291 --> 29:08.374
Anybody see any good movies?

29:08.375 --> 29:10.165
Did I miss your birthday?

29:10.166 --> 29:12.999
Strange weather we're having, isn't it?

29:13.000 --> 29:15.333
Ahh!

29:18.791 --> 29:19.666
Run!

29:22.666 --> 29:26.291
- It's just a dream. It's just a dream.
- Feels pretty real to me.

29:30.708 --> 29:33.332
- What happened?
- I almost had a nightmare in my pants.

29:33.333 --> 29:36.624
No, why did I wake up when you woke up?

29:36.625 --> 29:38.665
Who cares? That was terrifying!

29:38.666 --> 29:40.374
I'm never going back there again.

29:40.375 --> 29:42.790
Good. Then you can't ruin my dreams.

29:42.791 --> 29:45.790
I could really use a friend
who smells like processed meat right now.

29:45.791 --> 29:48.500
I'm coming for you, Baloney Tony!

29:54.125 --> 29:56.833
Come on.

29:57.833 --> 29:58.833
Got ya!

30:00.875 --> 30:02.000
You're alive!

30:03.875 --> 30:04.875
Yeah.

30:06.791 --> 30:08.083
Oh, no.

30:08.625 --> 30:10.332
Look who's back!

30:10.333 --> 30:11.874
Wait. What are you doing?

30:11.875 --> 30:15.041
Well, it says here because
we said the chant at the same time,

30:15.625 --> 30:16.958
we're now psychically linked.

30:18.166 --> 30:21.541
Which means I can't get to the Sandman
unless we go back.

30:22.083 --> 30:23.374
- Together.
- Nope.

30:23.375 --> 30:27.040
Nuh-uh! No way I'm going back there.
Not in a million years.

30:27.041 --> 30:28.457
Come on, Elliot.

30:28.458 --> 30:32.000
You want me to face that Nightmara thing
just so you can get your own room?

30:33.708 --> 30:34.625
Yes.

30:35.208 --> 30:37.124
Sorry. Not gonna happen.

30:37.125 --> 30:39.957
I'm never gonna sleep,
and you can't make me.

30:39.958 --> 30:41.208
You wanna bet?

30:46.208 --> 30:48.249
Tiny turtle sleep machine.

30:48.250 --> 30:50.583
It's worked since you were a baby.

30:51.166 --> 30:53.999
No, no, no. It's too powerful. You can't!

30:54.000 --> 30:55.832
- Yes.
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

30:55.833 --> 30:57.665
- I...
- Stevie!

30:57.666 --> 30:58.707
...can.

30:58.708 --> 30:59.749
No!

30:59.750 --> 31:01.375
Elliot!

31:02.416 --> 31:04.500
We have to get to the Sandman.

31:05.000 --> 31:05.833
No.

31:06.500 --> 31:08.250
I don't wanna go back!

31:13.916 --> 31:14.916
No!

31:16.833 --> 31:18.708
Yes!

31:21.250 --> 31:22.583
Uh...

31:23.500 --> 31:25.958
Sleep, I have vanquished you!

31:26.541 --> 31:27.874
Oh, hey, Dad.

31:27.875 --> 31:30.083
I'm gonna make some coffee. You want some?

31:38.583 --> 31:41.708
<i>Don't you wish
Your pizza was hot like me?</i>

31:42.625 --> 31:46.000
<i>Don't you wish your pizza
Was a freak like me?</i>

31:46.541 --> 31:47.541
<i>Don't cha?</i>

31:50.666 --> 31:53.124
Dad, you gotta get up there on the drums.

31:53.125 --> 31:56.082
That creepy old-timey bear is blowing it.

31:56.083 --> 31:59.665
Hey, hey. Your mom and I
used to open for Mustache Moe, okay?

31:59.666 --> 32:01.875
Played our first gig right there.

32:04.958 --> 32:07.957
Hello. You're so cute.

32:07.958 --> 32:10.540
I'm so sorry I have to bash your face in.

32:10.541 --> 32:13.999
Sorry! Sorry! Sorry!
Sorry! Sorry! Sorry! Sorry!

32:14.000 --> 32:16.583
So, Dad, I've been thinking.

32:17.166 --> 32:20.082
What if you and Mom
got the band back together?

32:20.083 --> 32:22.665
Like, at night, after school?
You guys are so good.

32:22.666 --> 32:24.790
I could harmonize. What do you say?

32:24.791 --> 32:26.875
I wish it were that easy, kiddo.

32:28.166 --> 32:30.957
But you guys are fine, right?

32:30.958 --> 32:34.332
I mean, it's not like
Mom's gonna move to Duluth,

32:34.333 --> 32:35.999
and you're staying here,

32:36.000 --> 32:38.208
'cause that's just crazy, right?

32:43.375 --> 32:44.332
Right?

32:44.333 --> 32:45.499
Ah, Stevie.

32:45.500 --> 32:48.416
You know, it's like, uh...

32:49.166 --> 32:51.040
It's like when I'm writing a song.

32:51.041 --> 32:55.040
You know, sometimes it just works,
and it's easy, and I know what comes next.

32:55.041 --> 32:59.499
And-- And other times I don't,
and I get totally stuck.

32:59.500 --> 33:01.790
And it's impossible to see the next note.

33:01.791 --> 33:03.665
And before you know it,
it's been three hours,

33:03.666 --> 33:06.040
and I'm just staring at a wall

33:06.041 --> 33:09.458
because I can't figure out
how to finish the song, and... and...

33:10.958 --> 33:13.000
And I'm not helping, am I?

33:16.208 --> 33:18.125
I just don't want you to worry, honey.

33:18.958 --> 33:21.040
Imposter!

33:21.041 --> 33:24.790
If you're the real Polly,
what's your favorite pizza topping?

33:24.791 --> 33:26.790
Uh, crackers?

33:26.791 --> 33:28.874
Your last name is Pepperoni!

33:28.875 --> 33:29.999
Get her!

33:30.000 --> 33:33.041
No, no, no, not the beak!
It comes out of my paycheck.

33:33.833 --> 33:36.374
- You suck!
- I hate my life.

33:36.375 --> 33:40.291
Elliot, don't jump on his face.
Come on, buddy!

33:41.041 --> 33:42.749
Now I've gotta slip the parrot a 20.

33:42.750 --> 33:45.666
<i>Polly's Pizzeria, a place for family fun!</i>

34:01.916 --> 34:03.750
What's up, turd nugget?

34:04.458 --> 34:05.916
Close the door.

34:11.250 --> 34:12.208
D'oh!

34:18.000 --> 34:19.208
<i>Don't cha?</i>

34:20.208 --> 34:23.999
Uh, are you still mad at me for waking up?
Or just normal mad?

34:24.000 --> 34:25.500
Mom got the job.

34:27.625 --> 34:28.750
In Duluth.

34:29.333 --> 34:30.374
Huh?

34:30.375 --> 34:32.333
She texted Dad.

34:33.416 --> 34:34.416
I saw it.

34:35.583 --> 34:38.457
But I can't move to the city.

34:38.458 --> 34:41.207
My skin will lose
its beautiful country glow!

34:41.208 --> 34:43.832
Elliot, we're in serious trouble.

34:43.833 --> 34:45.374
Dad doesn't wanna go.

34:45.375 --> 34:48.500
They've been fighting a lot, and I think

34:49.541 --> 34:51.666
they're splitting up.

34:53.541 --> 34:54.457
What?

34:54.458 --> 34:57.332
Yeah. We'll have to go to a new school,

34:57.333 --> 34:59.999
make new friends.
We'll have to go between their houses,

35:00.000 --> 35:02.874
and you know Dad's not gonna build us
a bunk bed that's up to code.

35:02.875 --> 35:04.374
And what if they get remarried,

35:04.375 --> 35:07.957
and we get step-siblings,
and they're lazy, and they hate magic,

35:07.958 --> 35:10.624
and everything will be split
and weird and-- and--

35:10.625 --> 35:12.375
Stevie.

35:13.291 --> 35:14.583
Are you and me

35:15.750 --> 35:17.166
gonna split up?

35:19.458 --> 35:20.500
I don't know.

35:23.708 --> 35:25.750
I know you're scared,

35:26.875 --> 35:29.874
but we have a chance to save our family,

35:29.875 --> 35:32.208
if we can just find the Sandman.

36:40.625 --> 36:43.416
<i>Polly's Pizzeria, a place for family fun!</i>

36:44.875 --> 36:48.832
<i>Don't you wish your pizza
Was cheesy like me?</i>

36:48.833 --> 36:52.332
<i>Don't you wish your pizza
Was fresh like me...</i>

36:52.333 --> 36:55.707
Okay. We're gonna stay asleep
this time, right?

36:55.708 --> 36:56.624
Right.

36:56.625 --> 36:58.540
- No matter what?
- No matter what.

36:58.541 --> 36:59.874
No matter what!

36:59.875 --> 37:01.040
No, Elliot!

37:01.041 --> 37:04.332
Dang, this new generation is way--

37:04.333 --> 37:06.790
Dang it. Come on.
Keep it together, Baloney Anthony.

37:06.791 --> 37:10.375
Okay.

37:11.541 --> 37:12.790
Eh, whatever.

37:12.791 --> 37:13.915
You good?

37:13.916 --> 37:15.582
Yeah.

37:15.583 --> 37:18.040
Listen, Joanne,
I know you've always looked up to me.

37:18.041 --> 37:20.332
- No, not at all.
- So I'm gonna let you in on a secret.

37:20.333 --> 37:23.040
If you really wanna find the Sandman,
you gotta stop dreaming

37:23.041 --> 37:26.749
and start lucid dreaming.

37:26.750 --> 37:27.874
Lucid dreaming?

37:27.875 --> 37:31.665
Mm-hmm. If you concentrate hard enough,
you can take control of your dreams.

37:31.666 --> 37:35.165
You just gotta have an open mind.
Elliot knows what I'm talking about.

37:35.166 --> 37:38.124
His mind is like a big,
endless, open field of nothing.

37:38.125 --> 37:39.040
That's right.

37:39.041 --> 37:40.499
But you. You're way too...

37:40.500 --> 37:42.415
"My system is overloaded."

37:42.416 --> 37:44.707
"Need to spreadsheet my feelings."

37:44.708 --> 37:47.708
Okay, that's enough.

37:48.416 --> 37:49.957
Hey, Nightmara!

37:49.958 --> 37:54.208
We have a date with the Sandman,
and you can't stop us!

37:56.416 --> 38:02.832
<i>Don't you wish your pizza was awful?</i>

38:02.833 --> 38:05.582
I'm rooting for ya, E!

38:05.583 --> 38:08.458
You got this, buddy!

38:12.916 --> 38:15.207
Why do I get the feeling
it's payback time?

38:15.208 --> 38:19.582
Oh, hello. You're so cute.

38:19.583 --> 38:22.749
I'm so sorry I have to bash your face in.

38:22.750 --> 38:25.208
- No, no, no, no, no!
- Elliot, don't wake up!

38:29.250 --> 38:30.457
Elliot!

38:30.458 --> 38:34.707
It's gonna take a lot more than
some crappy bash-a-badgers to stop us.

38:34.708 --> 38:36.875
It's nap time.

38:38.791 --> 38:41.207
I don't need two eyes
to see that this is a bad idea.

38:41.208 --> 38:42.124
Tony!

38:42.125 --> 38:44.207
- Is she still back there?
- Who?

38:44.208 --> 38:49.082
Here's Granny!

38:49.083 --> 38:50.665
Wait! Grandma?

38:50.666 --> 38:54.040
Did you get the birthday card I sent?

38:54.041 --> 38:55.540
You're scared of Grandma?

38:55.541 --> 38:57.540
- Eh?
- Don't judge me!

38:57.541 --> 38:59.708
Eggxecute them!

39:00.958 --> 39:02.165
Hey, man, don't do this!

39:02.166 --> 39:05.040
I know you got a beautiful heart
next to that yummy custard!

39:05.041 --> 39:07.457
You dirty custard!

39:07.458 --> 39:08.999
Baloney Tony!

39:09.000 --> 39:12.040
Oh, my God!

39:12.041 --> 39:14.750
How hard is it to stay asleep?

39:16.250 --> 39:18.665
- Naked dream!
- What's so scary about this?

39:18.666 --> 39:20.457
Absolutely nothing.

39:20.458 --> 39:21.832
<i>Naked on aisle four.</i>

39:21.833 --> 39:25.207
<i>Stevie Ting is naked on aisle four.</i>

39:25.208 --> 39:27.165
I didn't know there was a test today.

39:27.166 --> 39:30.332
You're gonna get a B...

39:30.333 --> 39:31.999
...minus!

39:32.000 --> 39:34.165
No!

39:34.166 --> 39:37.207
Okay, those two were on me.

39:37.208 --> 39:40.582
Ah, I love the open sea!

39:40.583 --> 39:41.666
Holy mackerel!

39:44.250 --> 39:46.958
- Fish tickles!
- Abandon ship!

39:49.708 --> 39:51.499
Not this one again!

39:51.500 --> 39:53.250
Never trust a hot dog!

39:57.500 --> 39:59.750
You're not the real Polly.

40:10.250 --> 40:13.415
How many more nightmares
do we have to face?

40:13.416 --> 40:15.957
We need to keep going
until we don't wake up.

40:15.958 --> 40:18.332
Or we could give up
and go back to the naked dream.

40:18.333 --> 40:21.499
No one puts Frank in the corner.

40:21.500 --> 40:23.874
No, not Frank!

40:23.875 --> 40:25.665
Not Frank!

40:25.666 --> 40:28.374
Frank, come on!
We are from the doll community.

40:28.375 --> 40:30.333
We're stuffed with the same love.

40:33.208 --> 40:34.707
Stevie.

40:34.708 --> 40:36.999
I'm right here. Stay strong.

40:37.000 --> 40:40.665
I'm starting to think he's upset!

40:40.666 --> 40:42.374
Stay strong. Stay strong. Stay strong.

40:42.375 --> 40:44.125
Stay strong!

40:49.166 --> 40:50.166
Hmm?

40:57.750 --> 40:58.750
What the...

40:59.875 --> 41:01.583
That's it! Elliot!

41:02.583 --> 41:04.249
- Elliot.
- Sorry, what?

41:04.250 --> 41:07.790
If we hold hands and think
the same thing at the same time, we can...

41:07.791 --> 41:09.208
Lucid dream!

41:10.500 --> 41:11.374
Oh, man.

41:11.375 --> 41:13.415
Incoming!

41:13.416 --> 41:16.165
Run!

41:16.166 --> 41:18.374
Ha-ha!

41:18.375 --> 41:19.333
Bed!

41:30.041 --> 41:31.916
- Hey, girl!
- Whoo-hoo!

41:35.375 --> 41:38.457
Elliot, you know what it's time for?

41:38.458 --> 41:42.624
Dynamite...

41:42.625 --> 41:43.833
fists!

41:48.666 --> 41:51.333
Huh?

41:53.583 --> 41:54.499
Uh-oh.

41:54.500 --> 41:56.040
- Oh!
- Right.

41:56.041 --> 41:58.875
Dynamite fists!

42:12.208 --> 42:13.041
Cool.

42:15.625 --> 42:17.999
We did it!

42:18.000 --> 42:19.457
Whoa! W-w-wait!

42:19.458 --> 42:22.332
How about we turn off
the dynamite fists first?

42:22.333 --> 42:24.208
- Oh!
- Oh, right.

42:25.125 --> 42:27.874
I'm comfortable celebrating now.

42:27.875 --> 42:30.165
Oh, my gosh, Elliot! That was amazing!

42:30.166 --> 42:31.957
Frank was like...

42:31.958 --> 42:32.874
And we were like...

42:32.875 --> 42:34.040
We were like...

42:34.041 --> 42:35.707
- I was like...
- We were like...

42:35.708 --> 42:38.790
- And then you were like...
- I was-- You hear me, right? Hello.

42:38.791 --> 42:40.499
- And then we were like, yeah!
- Yeah!

42:40.500 --> 42:42.582
- Exploded!
- Boom!

42:42.583 --> 42:45.290
We are awesome!

42:45.291 --> 42:48.124
Yeah, I'm awesome. You're awesome.

42:48.125 --> 42:50.833
- She's almost awesome.
- Wait, what?

42:53.125 --> 42:55.708
Oh-ho-ho-ho-ho!

43:03.291 --> 43:04.333
Hey, Stevie.

43:05.166 --> 43:06.958
Do you think this is really gonna work?

43:10.625 --> 43:11.625
It has to.

43:24.750 --> 43:26.082
What's happening?

43:26.083 --> 43:28.540
Oh no! I thought we won!

43:28.541 --> 43:30.415
Elliot!

43:30.416 --> 43:32.875
Tony!

43:39.333 --> 43:40.541
<i>Wake up.</i>

43:41.125 --> 43:43.707
Don't wake up. Don't wake up.
Don't wake up. Don't wake up!

43:43.708 --> 43:45.416
Stevie!

43:47.208 --> 43:52.000
<i>Wake up.</i>

43:57.500 --> 44:00.666
<i>Wake up. Wake up.</i>

44:01.333 --> 44:02.583
<i>Wake up.</i>

44:03.541 --> 44:05.165
<i>Wake up.</i>

44:05.166 --> 44:06.833
<i>Wake up. Wake up.</i>

44:07.458 --> 44:11.250
<i>Wake up!</i>

44:32.666 --> 44:35.416
Huh?

44:43.208 --> 44:45.041
Well, we died.

44:46.083 --> 44:50.333
No, I think we actually made it.

44:52.166 --> 44:52.999
Elliot!

44:53.000 --> 44:55.332
You stayed asleep!

44:55.333 --> 44:56.666
I did!

45:00.583 --> 45:01.458
Whoa!

45:35.583 --> 45:38.083
Uh, now what?

45:57.833 --> 46:00.290
You're thinking jetpack, right?

46:00.291 --> 46:01.666
Well, I am now.

46:02.333 --> 46:04.540
Whoa! Cool!

46:04.541 --> 46:08.125
Elliot, we don't need jetpacks.

46:08.791 --> 46:10.791
Oh, right.

46:23.000 --> 46:23.875
Whoa!

46:27.708 --> 46:30.040
Blast off!

46:30.041 --> 46:31.582
Yeah!

46:31.583 --> 46:34.041
Wow!

46:35.333 --> 46:37.208
Whoo-hoo!

47:18.708 --> 47:19.999
Whoa!

47:20.000 --> 47:22.416
Cool!

47:34.375 --> 47:36.124
Oh, sorry.

47:36.125 --> 47:37.791
Oh.

47:46.250 --> 47:48.250
Sandlings...

47:49.750 --> 47:50.583
Hit it!

47:58.916 --> 48:01.165
<i>Mr. Sandman, that's me!</i>

48:01.166 --> 48:02.749
<i>Bringing the dreams</i>

48:02.750 --> 48:03.832
Not the right beat!

48:03.833 --> 48:06.874
<i>Blowin' your mind with make-believe</i>

48:06.875 --> 48:08.040
Not the right energy!

48:08.041 --> 48:11.207
<i>Fly in the sky or dance in the sea</i>

48:11.208 --> 48:12.290
That's just wrong.

48:12.291 --> 48:15.999
<i>How about the one
Where it's candy you sneeze?</i>

48:16.000 --> 48:19.499
- <i>Sometimes if I'm feeling extreme</i>
- Ooh!

48:19.500 --> 48:20.832
That's it!

48:20.833 --> 48:24.374
<i>I use this dolphin With awful hygiene</i>

48:24.375 --> 48:28.207
<i>Let's turn on my magic beams</i>

48:28.208 --> 48:30.749
<i>Mr. Sandman bringing</i>

48:30.750 --> 48:32.332
<i>Yes, I'm bringing</i>

48:32.333 --> 48:35.040
<i>Mr. Sandman</i>

48:35.041 --> 48:40.540
<i>Bringing your dreams</i>

48:40.541 --> 48:41.916
Ha-ha!

48:48.750 --> 48:49.832
- Wow!
- Yeah!

48:49.833 --> 48:52.250
Okay, back to work, everyone.

48:56.833 --> 49:00.040
Chad.

49:00.041 --> 49:02.666
- Chad, go make some dreams!
- What?

49:04.791 --> 49:07.040
Sandlings.

49:07.041 --> 49:10.999
Welcome to my sandcastle!

49:11.000 --> 49:15.374
Oh, it's been ages
since anyone's made it past Nightmara.

49:15.375 --> 49:18.249
You two are quite the team.

49:18.250 --> 49:20.582
Yeah, I guess we are.

49:20.583 --> 49:22.999
This is very exciting. Very exciting!

49:23.000 --> 49:26.208
So, what's your dream? Just name it.

49:26.791 --> 49:29.625
Um, our parents,

49:30.375 --> 49:33.541
I think they're splitting up.

49:34.625 --> 49:35.749
Oh my.

49:35.750 --> 49:40.083
Can you please just make us
a happy family again?

49:41.041 --> 49:42.083
Follow me.

49:42.666 --> 49:43.666
Wow.

49:44.625 --> 49:46.625
Whoop!

49:48.625 --> 49:51.458
Whoo-hoo! Hey, Stevie! Up here!

49:52.166 --> 49:54.000
Check it out!

49:56.875 --> 50:00.333
Look at me! A-ha!

50:01.125 --> 50:03.207
- Huh?
- Over here!

50:03.208 --> 50:06.041
All the blood is rushing to my brain!

50:08.083 --> 50:09.915
Oop! What's that thing?

50:09.916 --> 50:12.832
Oh, that. It's how we make dreams.

50:12.833 --> 50:15.332
Eh, pretty standard stuff, really.

50:15.333 --> 50:17.666
Let me show you how it works.

50:18.333 --> 50:22.040
You drop the sand cube thingy
into the kaleidoscope looking dealy.

50:22.041 --> 50:23.374
It falls down,

50:23.375 --> 50:27.749
and then some kind of magic, I don't know,
could be science or 5G broadband.

50:27.750 --> 50:29.749
No one really knows, really.

50:29.750 --> 50:33.165
But each dream is carefully crafted.

50:33.166 --> 50:37.541
Flying dreams, farting laser dreams.

50:38.625 --> 50:40.040
Dreams where, say,

50:40.041 --> 50:42.916
you save your secret crush
from a burning building.

50:44.500 --> 50:45.666
How's my hair?

50:46.541 --> 50:48.291
Who has those dreams?

50:49.291 --> 50:50.790
Say anything and you're dead.

50:50.791 --> 50:53.040
Don't you just love dreams?

50:53.041 --> 50:55.999
They show you
how perfect the world could be.

50:56.000 --> 50:58.707
How perfect it should be.

50:58.708 --> 51:02.415
So is this how you're gonna
keep our parents together?

51:02.416 --> 51:03.915
By just giving them a dream?

51:03.916 --> 51:05.124
Oh, no, no, no, no.

51:05.125 --> 51:08.500
For you, I have something much better.

51:22.416 --> 51:26.165
All you need to do is turn the hourglass.

51:26.166 --> 51:28.832
When the last grain of sand falls,

51:28.833 --> 51:33.708
your dreams will be sealed
into the fabric of reality.

51:34.583 --> 51:36.791
Ooh!

51:43.958 --> 51:46.958
Come on, give it a little push.

52:05.541 --> 52:07.040
Ha-ho!

52:07.041 --> 52:10.208
Now all you have to do is wake up.

52:11.666 --> 52:13.249
Thanks, Mr. Sandman.

52:13.250 --> 52:15.166
Sweet dreams.

52:32.000 --> 52:32.833
Huh?

52:39.500 --> 52:41.500
Uh, you're back early.

52:42.875 --> 52:44.833
I thought you were
gonna stay at your mom's.

52:45.416 --> 52:48.957
Well, I forgot
my mom's a recurring nightmare.

52:48.958 --> 52:51.833
Uh, that is my mother-in-law
you're talking about.

52:53.666 --> 52:55.791
And I got a little homesick.

52:59.875 --> 53:01.957
And I just made breakfast.
I'll get you a plate?

53:01.958 --> 53:03.000
We can do that!

53:03.833 --> 53:06.250
Oh, hey. Morning, guys.

53:13.541 --> 53:16.250
<i>Can you remember when we were young</i>

53:19.166 --> 53:21.750
<i>How our hands were made for holding on</i>

53:23.000 --> 53:27.208
<i>And all the love we had
Would never let it fall</i>

53:29.708 --> 53:32.208
<i>Do you remember how we held it all?</i>

53:33.541 --> 53:35.416
<i>Well, it still goes on</i>

53:36.333 --> 53:38.375
<i>Even when we won't</i>

53:39.458 --> 53:44.541
<i>When the light won't shine
On the love we wrote</i>

53:45.666 --> 53:50.625
<i>Even when the miles keep us
Further than we were</i>

53:51.500 --> 53:56.791
<i>We can still go back
To all the lessons that we learned</i>

53:57.625 --> 54:00.832
<i>It don't matter where we are</i>

54:00.833 --> 54:05.250
<i>Because we know that we'll still go on</i>

54:06.125 --> 54:08.333
<i>Anywhere we go</i>

54:09.666 --> 54:10.916
<i>And the holding on</i>

54:12.500 --> 54:14.458
<i>It will still go on</i>

54:18.458 --> 54:20.833
<i>If you still hold on</i>

54:23.500 --> 54:25.875
<i>It will still go on</i>

54:28.875 --> 54:31.333
<i>I keep holding on</i>

54:39.458 --> 54:41.208
We love you, buddy.

54:42.666 --> 54:44.457
Um, Mom.

54:44.458 --> 54:47.541
Are you really going to take the job?

54:48.125 --> 54:50.458
Um, well,

54:51.875 --> 54:52.708
maybe not.

55:01.375 --> 55:03.041
Oh, sweetie, is everything okay?

55:05.541 --> 55:07.125
Everything is perfect.

55:12.041 --> 55:13.166
Mm.

55:14.541 --> 55:17.625
Oh, I've always loved this photo.

55:45.166 --> 55:46.165
Good night, guys.

55:46.166 --> 55:47.125
Love you.

55:49.750 --> 55:52.250
Stevie, what's up?

55:53.541 --> 55:54.500
Nothing.

55:58.916 --> 56:00.166
That's weird.

56:01.291 --> 56:02.833
My stuff is all

56:03.833 --> 56:06.291
neat and clean.

56:07.166 --> 56:08.333
Barely There is

56:09.166 --> 56:10.250
all there.

56:13.625 --> 56:17.208
And Baloney Tony smells like lavender!

56:17.791 --> 56:20.249
Let's not panic.
He said he'd make our dreams come true.

56:20.250 --> 56:22.916
So that's why
things are a little different.

56:23.500 --> 56:24.833
Elliot, gimme my photo.

56:25.416 --> 56:27.832
Wait, wasn't this broken before?

56:27.833 --> 56:30.665
- Elliot, give it back.
- Stevie, none of this is real.

56:30.666 --> 56:32.165
No, it has to be.

56:32.166 --> 56:34.499
- This is all just another...
- Gimme my photo now!

56:34.500 --> 56:36.583
...stupid dream!

56:40.666 --> 56:41.957
What did you do?

56:41.958 --> 56:43.333
I don't know.

56:55.875 --> 56:57.999
What happened? What's wrong?

56:58.000 --> 57:01.499
It... was just another dream.

57:01.500 --> 57:03.457
I told you it wasn't real.

57:03.458 --> 57:05.874
You didn't stay long enough.

57:05.875 --> 57:10.332
You have to stay
until the last grain of sand falls.

57:10.333 --> 57:11.416
Then what?

57:12.416 --> 57:13.540
Then it's real?

57:13.541 --> 57:15.999
Well, then you forget that it's not.

57:16.000 --> 57:20.208
This is what it takes
to make your dreams come true, Stevie.

57:21.916 --> 57:24.665
Okay, then.

57:24.666 --> 57:26.082
This guy's cuckoo bananas.

57:26.083 --> 57:28.290
Love your theme song.
This was a fun adventure.

57:28.291 --> 57:30.541
But, uh, we gotta go.

57:31.208 --> 57:33.916
Stevie, listen to me.

57:34.666 --> 57:36.790
I know your parents' thoughts,

57:36.791 --> 57:39.040
their deepest desires.

57:39.041 --> 57:42.333
I know their dreams.

57:43.458 --> 57:47.416
And they don't include each other anymore.

57:50.250 --> 57:53.749
But it doesn't have to be that way.

57:53.750 --> 57:54.915
Stevie!

57:54.916 --> 57:57.041
Elliot, get on over here.

57:57.625 --> 57:59.208
It's all gonna be okay.

57:59.750 --> 58:02.540
Stay here with us, Stevie.
We'll have so much fun.

58:02.541 --> 58:05.791
Yeah, it'll be perfect.

58:10.375 --> 58:13.333
Stevie, wait. What are you doing?

58:14.458 --> 58:15.583
He's right.

58:17.333 --> 58:20.083
This is the only way
we can all stay together.

58:23.666 --> 58:27.208
But... this isn't real.

58:27.958 --> 58:29.374
We have to go back.

58:29.375 --> 58:32.208
To what? More fighting?

58:32.791 --> 58:35.208
Our family being torn apart?

58:37.375 --> 58:40.458
I don't wanna wake up to that.

58:49.083 --> 58:51.832
- I'm not gonna let you do this!
- Elliot, don't!

58:51.833 --> 58:52.957
Stevie, come on!

58:52.958 --> 58:54.915
Can you just not mess this up for me?

58:54.916 --> 58:56.707
I'm not trying to mess it up.

58:56.708 --> 59:00.000
Well, you are.
Just like you mess up everything.

59:01.833 --> 59:03.332
That's not true!

59:03.333 --> 59:04.374
Elliot, buddy.

59:04.375 --> 59:06.125
Elliot, stop it!

59:06.791 --> 59:08.957
- I said stop it!
- No!

59:08.958 --> 59:10.624
- Elliot!
- I'm not going home...

59:10.625 --> 59:12.750
- Just leave me alone!
- ...alone!

59:26.125 --> 59:28.041
Don't worry. He'll be okay.

59:28.625 --> 59:31.915
Oh, bug. You're safe here with us.

59:31.916 --> 59:33.875
Everything is gonna be okay now.

59:34.458 --> 59:36.665
Just a little while longer

59:36.666 --> 59:39.541
and your dream will finally come true.

59:52.708 --> 59:53.541
Stevie?

59:54.833 --> 59:57.125
No, no, no, no, no, come on!

59:57.875 --> 59:58.707
Wake up.

59:58.708 --> 01:00:01.249
Stevie, please.

01:00:01.250 --> 01:00:02.875
Wake up! Dad!

01:00:03.458 --> 01:00:05.499
Dad!

01:00:05.500 --> 01:00:07.375
Elliot, what's going on?

01:00:16.791 --> 01:00:18.708
Doctor said her vitals were fine.

01:00:19.833 --> 01:00:21.333
She just needs to wake up.

01:00:22.541 --> 01:00:25.333
I don't understand
how any of this happened.

01:00:27.833 --> 01:00:29.833
She made a wish

01:00:30.500 --> 01:00:32.083
for you to stay together

01:00:32.708 --> 01:00:35.083
so we could all be happy again.

01:00:45.416 --> 01:00:48.374
Okay, ready?

01:00:48.375 --> 01:00:51.457
Beautiful spatula flip
into a quadruple 1080 backspin!

01:00:51.458 --> 01:00:53.707
- And she sticks the landing!
- Oh-ho-ho-ho!

01:00:53.708 --> 01:00:55.165
The moment of truth.

01:00:55.166 --> 01:00:57.249
Will Stevie Ting be crowned

01:00:57.250 --> 01:01:00.208
the best French toast cook on the planet?

01:01:00.833 --> 01:01:02.082
Close.

01:01:02.083 --> 01:01:05.915
You know, tastes kinda fishy.

01:01:05.916 --> 01:01:07.415
- No, no, no, no! Human shield!
- No!

01:01:07.416 --> 01:01:09.082
Fish tickles!

01:01:09.083 --> 01:01:13.125
No, no, no, no! Never! Eat spatula!

01:01:14.541 --> 01:01:16.666
No, bedrooms are safe zones!

01:01:27.041 --> 01:01:29.833
My own room.

01:01:53.625 --> 01:01:55.500
What are you doing here?

01:01:59.125 --> 01:02:00.499
<i>That one, Stevie.</i>

01:02:00.500 --> 01:02:01.582
That one.

01:02:01.583 --> 01:02:03.291
I know! Quiet.

01:02:03.833 --> 01:02:05.750
This is my last dollar.

01:02:06.291 --> 01:02:08.000
It has to be perfect.

01:02:10.416 --> 01:02:12.583
Okay, yeah. Yeah!

01:02:14.541 --> 01:02:15.582
- Yes!
- I did it! I did it!

01:02:15.583 --> 01:02:18.790
Oh, yes, finally!

01:02:18.791 --> 01:02:19.708
No!

01:02:21.666 --> 01:02:22.874
It's okay.

01:02:22.875 --> 01:02:24.541
I'm never gonna get one.

01:02:28.750 --> 01:02:29.666
Here.

01:02:31.291 --> 01:02:32.416
You can have mine.

01:02:35.083 --> 01:02:37.375
But-- But he's your favorite.

01:02:38.166 --> 01:02:40.375
We can play with him together.

01:02:41.208 --> 01:02:43.708
Look, I gave him a baloney pocket.

01:02:50.583 --> 01:02:52.666
He'll always be there for you.

01:03:04.166 --> 01:03:06.291
Yeah, he will.

01:03:09.833 --> 01:03:11.291
His name's Tony.

01:03:11.791 --> 01:03:13.416
Baloney Tony.

01:03:14.708 --> 01:03:16.708
Baloney Tony.

01:03:28.833 --> 01:03:29.875
Elliot.

01:03:31.541 --> 01:03:32.916
I'm coming home.

01:03:39.000 --> 01:03:41.333
Oh, what?

01:03:42.750 --> 01:03:45.165
Huh?

01:03:45.166 --> 01:03:48.540
No! No! No, no, no!

01:03:48.541 --> 01:03:51.665
Sandman, I don't-- I don't want this.

01:03:51.666 --> 01:03:55.166
I-- I wanna go home. I want...

01:03:56.375 --> 01:03:57.541
Elliot.

01:03:58.625 --> 01:04:01.749
- Wait, was that?
- Oh, my gosh. Sweetie, we're right here.

01:04:01.750 --> 01:04:03.125
I'm coming for you, Stevie.

01:04:05.666 --> 01:04:08.124
Whoa! Uh, what's happening?

01:04:08.125 --> 01:04:10.207
The Sandman promised
to make her dream come true,

01:04:10.208 --> 01:04:13.082
but if the hourglass runs out,
she'll be stuck there forever!

01:04:13.083 --> 01:04:14.999
I-- I don't understand.

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:17.291
I don't have time to explain.
It's all in here.

01:04:18.708 --> 01:04:20.874
If you wanna help, grab that pillow.

01:04:20.875 --> 01:04:21.791
What?

01:04:23.541 --> 01:04:24.833
It's nap time.

01:04:27.375 --> 01:04:28.582
Is this real?

01:04:28.583 --> 01:04:31.124
Wait, didn't he say earlier
they did some kind of chant

01:04:31.125 --> 01:04:32.790
and ended up in the same dream?

01:04:32.791 --> 01:04:37.374
Yeah, but he also thinks butterflies are
made by the government to spy on us.

01:04:37.375 --> 01:04:38.915
I believe him.

01:04:38.916 --> 01:04:40.166
About the dream

01:04:41.000 --> 01:04:42.291
and the butterflies.

01:04:46.666 --> 01:04:48.790
I am pumped! What's the plan?

01:04:48.791 --> 01:04:52.583
We're gonna get through Nightmara
and bring Stevie home!

01:04:55.125 --> 01:04:56.833
Yeah, I'm out.

01:04:57.333 --> 01:04:58.540
Baloney Tony!

01:04:58.541 --> 01:05:02.250
- It's not you. It's me!
- Aww.

01:05:05.750 --> 01:05:06.875
Yah!

01:05:16.500 --> 01:05:19.457
I got you a video game, Elliot.

01:05:19.458 --> 01:05:22.541
But it's for the wrong console!

01:05:25.166 --> 01:05:26.541
Sorry, Grandma!

01:05:31.916 --> 01:05:33.208
Hmm?

01:05:36.250 --> 01:05:39.124
I can feel pain!

01:05:39.125 --> 01:05:41.541
I'll never eat another hot dog again.

01:05:56.125 --> 01:06:00.083
<i>Wake up. Wake up! Wake up!</i>

01:06:03.083 --> 01:06:05.416
<i>Wake up!</i>

01:06:07.958 --> 01:06:10.333
No!

01:06:10.916 --> 01:06:12.166
Please!

01:06:13.250 --> 01:06:15.083
Let me out of here.

01:06:20.958 --> 01:06:22.958
Oh. Elliot.

01:06:24.583 --> 01:06:25.958
I'm so sorry.

01:06:26.791 --> 01:06:29.458
You're better than any dream.

01:06:38.583 --> 01:06:39.708
Elliot!

01:06:51.291 --> 01:06:52.250
Oh.

01:06:53.166 --> 01:06:55.916
I'm sorry I said you mess everything up.

01:06:57.083 --> 01:06:58.166
You don't.

01:06:59.375 --> 01:07:00.916
You make it better.

01:07:03.291 --> 01:07:04.416
You do too.

01:07:10.333 --> 01:07:12.750
Hmm. I like
what you've done with the place.

01:07:14.916 --> 01:07:18.833
Wait, how did you get past Nightmara?

01:07:19.416 --> 01:07:20.625
Well...

01:07:21.708 --> 01:07:25.458
I'm not gonna stop
until I wake up my sister!

01:07:27.583 --> 01:07:29.833
<i>Elliot...</i>

01:07:35.916 --> 01:07:37.083
Oh, no!

01:07:41.333 --> 01:07:44.457
No, no, please! I'm so weak and pathetic.
Look at me. I'm so scared.

01:07:44.458 --> 01:07:46.874
I'm just a child.
A tiny, defenseless little child.

01:07:46.875 --> 01:07:48.583
I'm basically a baby!

01:07:50.583 --> 01:07:53.541
All right, all right, all right.
Don't hurt yourself, kid.

01:07:54.166 --> 01:07:55.708
I'm not gonna scare you.

01:07:57.500 --> 01:07:59.750
I've been protecting you.

01:08:00.708 --> 01:08:02.499
From the Sandman.

01:08:02.500 --> 01:08:05.249
Hmm. You're a lot smarter than you look.

01:08:05.250 --> 01:08:06.500
Yeah, I am.

01:08:07.000 --> 01:08:07.874
Oh, wait.

01:08:07.875 --> 01:08:11.499
You know, me and the Sandman,

01:08:11.500 --> 01:08:13.249
we used to be cool.

01:08:13.250 --> 01:08:14.749
Not friends or anything.

01:08:14.750 --> 01:08:16.665
I mean, I hate happy people.

01:08:16.666 --> 01:08:18.707
But he did his job.

01:08:18.708 --> 01:08:21.582
And I did mine. Then he decided

01:08:21.583 --> 01:08:25.291
dreamers didn't need nightmares,
'cause they were...

01:08:27.416 --> 01:08:28.750
...too scary.

01:08:29.958 --> 01:08:31.082
But he's wrong.

01:08:31.083 --> 01:08:32.749
Nightmares make us strong

01:08:32.750 --> 01:08:35.833
so we can face
what's really scary in life.

01:08:36.416 --> 01:08:37.833
The unknown.

01:08:38.833 --> 01:08:41.832
When you don't know
what's making that sound under the bed

01:08:41.833 --> 01:08:43.040
or what's in the shadows...

01:08:43.041 --> 01:08:45.582
...or... or what comes next.

01:08:45.583 --> 01:08:48.833
I mean, it freaks you out so much.

01:08:51.333 --> 01:08:54.375
Hmm. You wanna
know how you get through it?

01:08:57.500 --> 01:09:00.958
You find something
that's always been there for you.

01:09:01.791 --> 01:09:05.457
Right in the middle of all the chaos,

01:09:05.458 --> 01:09:09.291
you find that constant,
unchangeable feeling...

01:09:11.958 --> 01:09:13.750
<i>and you hold onto it.</i>

01:09:15.416 --> 01:09:17.125
<i>You hold onto each other.</i>

01:09:24.375 --> 01:09:25.207
Oh, no!

01:09:25.208 --> 01:09:26.874
What rubbish!

01:09:26.875 --> 01:09:29.624
Nightmara isn't protecting you.

01:09:29.625 --> 01:09:33.791
She's preventing you
from the ultimate dream come true.

01:09:34.583 --> 01:09:37.790
Sorry, but it's time for me to wake up.

01:09:37.791 --> 01:09:39.957
Let's break the hourglass and go home.

01:09:39.958 --> 01:09:41.457
No!

01:09:41.458 --> 01:09:42.375
Elliot!

01:09:43.833 --> 01:09:44.666
Stevie!

01:09:45.541 --> 01:09:47.791
Oh!

01:09:49.750 --> 01:09:51.582
- Got ya!
- Whoa!

01:09:51.583 --> 01:09:53.666
- You thinking what I'm thinking?
- Yep!

01:09:57.291 --> 01:09:58.790
Jetpack! I'm thinking jetpack!

01:09:58.791 --> 01:10:00.874
What? Last time
you said we didn't need jetpacks!

01:10:00.875 --> 01:10:03.040
This is a different situation!

01:10:03.041 --> 01:10:04.915
Rescue mission!

01:10:04.916 --> 01:10:07.540
Baloney Tony, I knew you'd come back.

01:10:07.541 --> 01:10:10.791
Really? 'Cause I questioned it
right up to the last second.

01:10:11.375 --> 01:10:12.665
Get us to the hourglass.

01:10:12.666 --> 01:10:14.458
On it.

01:10:23.958 --> 01:10:25.875
Oh!

01:10:27.250 --> 01:10:30.333
Ha-ha-ha!
That's how you drive a bed. Uh-oh.

01:10:45.416 --> 01:10:47.333
Tony!

01:10:51.375 --> 01:10:52.541
Stevie!

01:10:56.166 --> 01:10:58.999
Whoa! Respect.

01:10:59.000 --> 01:10:59.958
Come on.

01:11:04.000 --> 01:11:05.624
You got this, Stevie!

01:11:05.625 --> 01:11:07.249
Oh, no, you don't.

01:11:07.250 --> 01:11:08.249
Yah!

01:11:08.250 --> 01:11:10.791
Sandlings!

01:11:12.041 --> 01:11:13.000
Stop them!

01:11:21.458 --> 01:11:22.291
Oh, no!

01:11:28.833 --> 01:11:30.791
Chad?

01:11:40.916 --> 01:11:43.041
Oh, no, no, no!

01:11:46.541 --> 01:11:48.666
Nighty-night.

01:11:51.041 --> 01:11:51.958
What?

01:11:55.916 --> 01:11:57.540
How did you get in here?

01:11:57.541 --> 01:12:01.625
I am a dad with two kids!

01:12:02.208 --> 01:12:04.040
I'm always down to sleep.

01:12:04.041 --> 01:12:06.875
This is my dream!

01:12:08.625 --> 01:12:11.458
Nope, it's our dream now.

01:12:13.833 --> 01:12:15.708
You have a little crusty in your eye.

01:12:17.166 --> 01:12:18.750
Come on, guys, we got this!

01:12:19.750 --> 01:12:20.874
Mom?

01:12:20.875 --> 01:12:22.249
They made it!

01:12:22.250 --> 01:12:25.874
Ha-ha! Never mess with Mrs. Joanne.

01:12:25.875 --> 01:12:27.832
- Ah, Jenn!
- Oh, right!

01:12:27.833 --> 01:12:30.500
Need a little backup?

01:12:31.916 --> 01:12:34.583
Hold on!

01:12:38.250 --> 01:12:41.833
It would probably be irresponsible
for me to push this.

01:12:42.916 --> 01:12:43.832
Uh-oh.

01:12:43.833 --> 01:12:45.375
Yes!

01:13:01.250 --> 01:13:02.625
We're not gonna make it!

01:13:03.916 --> 01:13:06.457
No, no, no!

01:13:06.458 --> 01:13:08.083
No!

01:13:38.875 --> 01:13:41.499
Oh, yeah! Cutting it super close.

01:13:41.500 --> 01:13:43.291
Oh, I'm gonna need a nap after this.

01:13:44.333 --> 01:13:48.458
Stevie, I just wanted you to be happy.

01:13:49.166 --> 01:13:51.707
I want everyone to be happy.

01:13:51.708 --> 01:13:52.749
Happy!

01:13:52.750 --> 01:13:54.957
Chad.

01:13:54.958 --> 01:13:56.707
Put me down. Chad.

01:13:56.708 --> 01:13:59.415
Chad! Don't make me get the vacuum. Chad!

01:13:59.416 --> 01:14:02.416
Oh, my gosh, Stevie. You're okay.

01:14:04.666 --> 01:14:07.333
- Dad, stop!
- Never!

01:14:09.041 --> 01:14:10.500
Oh, Stevie.

01:14:12.791 --> 01:14:15.041
I know you've been trying
to hold us together.

01:14:16.958 --> 01:14:21.500
And hearing about all this change
must be so scary for you.

01:14:23.083 --> 01:14:24.416
But listen to me.

01:14:25.083 --> 01:14:27.083
No matter what happens,

01:14:28.750 --> 01:14:30.416
we will always love you,

01:14:31.833 --> 01:14:35.083
and we will always be a family.

01:14:38.250 --> 01:14:39.250
I know.

01:14:46.625 --> 01:14:49.333
Mom punched the Sandman.

01:14:55.500 --> 01:14:57.582
It's so beautiful!

01:14:57.583 --> 01:14:59.833
Is that--

01:15:03.000 --> 01:15:04.624
Baloney Tony.

01:15:04.625 --> 01:15:05.916
What's up, Big Mike?

01:15:09.875 --> 01:15:12.541
Thank you, Tony.

01:15:13.208 --> 01:15:14.333
You're welcome,

01:15:15.416 --> 01:15:16.375
Stevie.

01:15:19.750 --> 01:15:21.541
I'll see you in your dreams, kid.

01:15:31.208 --> 01:15:35.125
Dynamite fists!

01:15:56.166 --> 01:15:58.457
You know you're gonna miss
sharing a room with me.

01:15:58.458 --> 01:16:01.665
Miss your stinky feet and stinky meats?
I don't think so.

01:16:01.666 --> 01:16:05.332
Well, in case you do, I made you this.

01:16:05.333 --> 01:16:08.291
Oh! You-- You shouldn't have.

01:16:08.791 --> 01:16:10.749
I call it Melliot.

01:16:10.750 --> 01:16:13.374
Part melon, part Elliot.

01:16:13.375 --> 01:16:15.750
You have to keep it on ice
so my head doesn't die.

01:16:16.833 --> 01:16:18.249
- Okay, I see it.
- Okay.

01:16:18.250 --> 01:16:19.957
- Be careful. Okay.
- Yeah. Easy.

01:16:19.958 --> 01:16:22.332
<i>So, yeah, we're moving to Duluth.</i>

01:16:22.333 --> 01:16:26.082
<i>Mom took the job,
and Dad's gonna start a new band there.</i>

01:16:26.083 --> 01:16:27.499
Oh, right! Got it, yeah.

01:16:27.500 --> 01:16:29.040
<i>As for the two of them...</i>

01:16:29.041 --> 01:16:30.832
- Other left.
- That's still not my left.

01:16:30.833 --> 01:16:32.707
- Okay, just bring it this way.
- No, no, no, no!

01:16:32.708 --> 01:16:35.665
<i>They're still figuring things out.</i>

01:16:35.666 --> 01:16:38.290
- Got it? Okay.
- Watch out for the...

01:16:38.291 --> 01:16:41.540
- Here we are. Ready? One, two, three!
- <i>And that's okay.</i>

01:16:41.541 --> 01:16:42.458
Up and over.

01:16:44.833 --> 01:16:46.415
- Good job.
- Okay.

01:16:46.416 --> 01:16:48.708
Whew!

01:17:00.666 --> 01:17:01.875
Is this crazy?

01:17:03.333 --> 01:17:04.666
Cuckoo bananas.

01:17:07.041 --> 01:17:08.333
But it's worth a shot.

01:17:20.291 --> 01:17:23.916
<i>So it turns out my dreams
were trying to tell me something.</i>

01:17:24.916 --> 01:17:26.833
<i>Life isn't perfect.</i>

01:17:28.125 --> 01:17:30.166
<i>And neither are we.</i>

01:17:31.166 --> 01:17:35.333
<i>But no matter how it changes,
we'll always have each other.</i>

01:17:38.041 --> 01:17:40.375
<i>And you can't get any better than that.</i>

01:17:41.916 --> 01:17:44.083
<i>Not even in your dreams.</i>

01:17:47.875 --> 01:17:50.790
Oh, no! Stop! Wait, wait! No!

01:17:50.791 --> 01:17:52.207
- Uh-oh.
- Michael!

01:17:52.208 --> 01:17:53.957
Dad! Whoa!

01:17:53.958 --> 01:17:56.540
Sorry, sorry. Oh, that can't be good.

01:17:56.541 --> 01:17:58.208
Oh, gosh!

01:18:00.958 --> 01:18:04.415
<i>Came in like a vision
From the old west wind</i>

01:18:04.416 --> 01:18:09.000
<i>Like a bright new dream
That I was stepping in</i>

01:18:09.583 --> 01:18:12.665
<i>I saw your face
And I knew it was a sign</i>

01:18:12.666 --> 01:18:17.291
<i>And I still think about that moment
All of the time</i>

01:18:26.333 --> 01:18:30.540
<i>You know that
I could never make this up</i>

01:18:30.541 --> 01:18:34.500
<i>I found the reason
I'm not giving it up</i>

01:18:35.125 --> 01:18:38.332
<i>I felt the fever
When I knew he was mine</i>

01:18:38.333 --> 01:18:39.249
<i>Oh, I</i>

01:18:39.250 --> 01:18:42.500
<i>I'm gonna love you for a long time</i>

01:18:43.583 --> 01:18:46.832
<i>And in the morning when I'm waking up</i>

01:18:46.833 --> 01:18:51.332
<i>I swear that you're the first thing
That I'm thinking of</i>

01:18:51.333 --> 01:18:55.415
<i>I feel it in my body
Know it in my mind</i>

01:18:55.416 --> 01:19:00.333
<i>Oh, I... I'm gonna
Love you for a long time</i>

01:19:01.458 --> 01:19:04.875
<i>I'm gonna love you for a long time</i>

01:19:05.625 --> 01:19:09.333
<i>I'm gonna love you for a long time</i>

01:19:13.041 --> 01:19:16.749
<i>Oh, I never knew it
Yeah, you took me by surprise</i>

01:19:16.750 --> 01:19:20.916
<i>While I was getting lost
So deep inside your diamond eyes</i>

01:19:22.041 --> 01:19:25.249
<i>So many things that I still wanna say</i>

01:19:25.250 --> 01:19:29.500
<i>And if devotion is a river
Then I'm floating away</i>

01:19:30.291 --> 01:19:33.332
<i>And in the morning when you pick me up</i>

01:19:33.333 --> 01:19:37.665
<i>And all the world is quiet
Except the morning dove</i>

01:19:37.666 --> 01:19:41.915
<i>I feel it in my body
Know it in my mind</i>

01:19:41.916 --> 01:19:43.999
<i>Oh, I</i>

01:19:44.000 --> 01:19:47.375
<i>I'm gonna love you for a long time</i>

01:19:48.375 --> 01:19:51.375
<i>I'm gonna love you for a long time</i>

01:19:52.125 --> 01:19:54.707
Okay, here we go.

01:19:54.708 --> 01:19:56.249
Dad, I'm hungry.

01:19:56.250 --> 01:19:57.790
Mom, can I drive?

01:19:57.791 --> 01:19:59.207
Uh, you're 12.

01:19:59.208 --> 01:20:01.040
But I drove a flying bed.

01:20:01.041 --> 01:20:03.625
And cars are basically beds with wheels.

01:20:22.416 --> 01:20:23.541
Meh.

01:20:39.916 --> 01:20:42.999
<i>Don't worry about me
Yeah, I'll be fine</i>

01:20:43.000 --> 01:20:45.832
<i>I read enough books for seven lives</i>

01:20:45.833 --> 01:20:48.749
<i>These walls keep singing back to me</i>

01:20:48.750 --> 01:20:51.707
<i>Like la-di-di-da if you dream</i>

01:20:51.708 --> 01:20:54.457
<i>Quiet like a mouse in a world so loud</i>

01:20:54.458 --> 01:20:57.249
<i>But life's too short
To not scream and shout</i>

01:20:57.250 --> 01:21:00.124
<i>I know that I'll make it out okay</i>

01:21:00.125 --> 01:21:03.082
<i>I'm dancing my way through every day</i>

01:21:03.083 --> 01:21:07.000
<i>'Cause I sleep to dream</i>

01:21:07.791 --> 01:21:09.791
<i>Of you and me</i>

01:21:14.000 --> 01:21:18.500
<i>Yeah, every night I sleep to dream</i>

01:21:19.166 --> 01:21:21.083
<i>Of you and me</i>

01:21:26.041 --> 01:21:28.874
<i>I'm drawn to you
Like a moth to a flame</i>

01:21:28.875 --> 01:21:31.749
<i>I'm yearning
I'm burning up for you, babe</i>

01:21:31.750 --> 01:21:35.291
<i>Heard that's the definition
Of you're insane, ha!</i>

01:21:35.958 --> 01:21:40.415
<i>I guess I'm insane for you</i>

01:21:40.416 --> 01:21:43.290
<i>Don't mind</i>

01:21:43.291 --> 01:21:48.957
<i>Let's pass the time</i>

01:21:48.958 --> 01:21:53.000
<i>So I sleep to dream</i>

01:21:53.791 --> 01:21:55.583
<i>Of you and me</i>

01:22:00.000 --> 01:22:04.583
<i>Yeah, every night I sleep to dream</i>

01:22:05.250 --> 01:22:07.083
<i>Of you and me</i>

01:22:12.708 --> 01:22:16.415
<i>I sleep to dream</i>

01:22:16.416 --> 01:22:18.958
<i>Of you and me</i>

01:22:24.000 --> 01:22:27.833
<i>I sleep to dream</i>

01:22:28.333 --> 01:22:30.250
<i>Of you and me</i>

01:22:43.166 --> 01:22:46.999
<i>Don't you wish
Your pizza was cheesy like me?</i>

01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:50.999
<i>Don't you wish
Your pizza was fresh like me?</i>

01:22:51.000 --> 01:22:53.000
<i>Don't cha?</i>

01:22:55.000 --> 01:22:56.708
<i>Don't cha?</i>

01:22:57.875 --> 01:23:00.708
<i>I know you like it</i>

01:23:01.625 --> 01:23:04.000
<i>I know you do</i>

01:23:05.625 --> 01:23:08.915
<i>That's why whenever it's time to eat</i>

01:23:08.916 --> 01:23:11.833
<i>We make it for you</i>

01:23:13.125 --> 01:23:15.958
<i>And I know you want it</i>

01:23:17.083 --> 01:23:19.583
<i>It's easy to see</i>

01:23:21.333 --> 01:23:23.624
<i>And we know all of your favorites</i>

01:23:23.625 --> 01:23:27.458
<i>Pineapple, pepperoni, and cheese</i>

01:23:30.041 --> 01:23:33.874
<i>Don't you wish
Your pizza was cheesy like me?</i>

01:23:33.875 --> 01:23:38.958
<i>Don't you wish Your pizza was off like me?</i>

01:23:39.500 --> 01:23:40.874
<i>Don't you wish</i>

01:23:40.875 --> 01:23:47.958
<i>Your pizza was awful?</i>
